select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'ผู้ป่วยอายุ 25 ปี Type 1 DM uncontrolled HbA1c 11.4 + multiple admit DKA + history of acute MI 1 year ago + ESRD on dialysis 2 years

Referral for kidney + pancreas transplant evaluation

คำถาม: pre-transplant workup + integrative considerations', '[{"label":"A","text":"Single organ transplant only"},{"label":"B","text":"**Simultaneous Pancreas-Kidney (SPK) transplant evaluation — integrative approach**: (1) **Candidacy assessment for SPK**: - Type 1 DM with ESRD - Brittle DM with poor quality of life (hypoglycemia unawareness, severe complications) - No major medical/surgical contraindications - Adequate functional status to undergo surgery + immunosuppression - Psychological + social support; (2) **Pre-transplant evaluation comprehensive**: - **Cardiac**: stress test (often pharmacologic — adenosine, dobutamine); coronary angiogram given prior MI (recurrent ischemia risk); echo (LV function, valves); 24h Holter if arrhythmia history - **Pulmonary**: PFT; CXR - **Infectious**: HIV, HBV, HCV, CMV, EBV, VZV, TB (IGRA/skin test), syphilis, strongyloides (depending on region); vaccination updates - **Cancer screening**: age-appropriate (colonoscopy, mammogram, Pap, PSA), thorough skin exam - **Endocrine**: thyroid, parathyroid (HPT common in ESRD) - **GI**: hepatitis serology + LFT; H. pylori; - **Vascular**: peripheral arterial — both for transplant access + future considerations - **Dental**: clearance, source control - **Psychiatric / psychosocial**: depression, anxiety, substance use, adherence assessment, support system - **Nutrition**: optimize - **Smoking cessation absolute**; (3) **Listing for transplant** — UNOS / OPTN matching system; - HLA typing, panel reactive antibodies (PRA), crossmatch - Allocation algorithm by region; - Wait list management; (4) **Surgical considerations**: - Pancreas transplant + kidney transplant — combined operation - Pancreas: portal vs systemic venous drainage; bladder vs enteric exocrine drainage - Kidney: heterotopic in iliac fossa - Iliac vessel access + arterial reconstruction; (5) **Immunosuppression** post-transplant: - Induction: anti-thymocyte globulin (ATG) or basiliximab - Maintenance: tacrolimus + mycophenolate + steroid (taper) - Adjustments per complications - Lifelong; (6) **Outcomes**: - SPK > Pancreas alone in long-term graft survival - 5-year patient survival 90%+, pancreas graft 70-80%, kidney 80-85% - Quality of life: insulin-free, improved DM complications progression - Hypoglycemia unawareness resolved typically; (7) **Post-transplant management**: - Immunosuppression monitoring (drug levels) - Rejection surveillance (creatinine, amylase, glucose) - Infection prophylaxis (PJP — TMP-SMX; CMV — valganciclovir; fungal — fluconazole) - Cancer surveillance (increased risk) - Cardiovascular risk management - Lifestyle - Adherence support; (8) **Family + support involvement** essential; (9) **Long-term complications**: chronic rejection, infections, malignancy (especially skin, PTLD), recurrence of underlying disease (rare in T1DM)"},{"label":"C","text":"No transplant consideration"},{"label":"D","text":"Dialysis lifelong only"},{"label":"E","text":"Discharge home with hospice referral"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Simultaneous Pancreas-Kidney (SPK) Transplantation** — option for selected T1DM with ESRD: free from dialysis + insulin; improved QOL + survival vs dialysis alone or kidney alone for many. **Indications**: 1. T1DM with ESRD (creatinine clearance < 20-30, on dialysis or pre-emptive) 2. Brittle T1DM with hypoglycemia unawareness or severe complications without ESRD (pancreas alone — PA — option, but lower graft survival) **Patient selection considerations**: - Cardiac risk significant in DM patients — comprehensive evaluation - Vascular disease assessment - Psychosocial readiness + adherence - Avoid in active malignancy, active infection, severe non-correctable comorbidity, substance use **Three main pancreas transplant types**: 1. **SPK** (Simultaneous Pancreas-Kidney) — best graft survival of pancreas options 2. **PAK** (Pancreas After Kidney) — if pancreas needs after prior kidney transplant 3. **PA / PTA** (Pancreas Transplant Alone) — for hypoglycemia unawareness without ESRD; lower graft survival **Surgical technique variations**: - **Exocrine drainage**: enteric (most common modern — to Roux limb of jejunum) vs bladder (older — easier monitoring of urinary amylase but UTI + dehydration + acidosis problems) - **Endocrine drainage**: portal (more physiologic) vs systemic (iliac vein — more common) - Concurrent kidney transplant to ipsilateral or contralateral iliac fossa **Immunosuppression** typical: - Induction: ATG (anti-thymocyte globulin) or basiliximab (anti-IL-2R) - Maintenance: tacrolimus + mycophenolate + steroid (often tapered to low-dose or stopped) **Outcomes (USA, UNOS data)**: - 5-yr patient survival ~ 90%+ - 5-yr pancreas graft survival ~ 70-80% - 5-yr kidney graft survival ~ 80-85% - Insulin-free for vast majority while graft functions - Improved diabetic complication progression (nephropathy, retinopathy, neuropathy) - Resolved hypoglycemia unawareness **Post-transplant management**: - Immunosuppression monitoring + adjustment - Rejection surveillance: creatinine, glucose, amylase (pancreas) - Infection prophylaxis: PJP, CMV, fungal - Vaccine schedule update - Cancer surveillance (skin especially, PTLD) - Cardiovascular risk - Adherence support **Islet cell transplantation** — alternative to whole-organ pancreas; minimally invasive (percutaneous portal vein infusion); good for selected (hypoglycemia unawareness without ESRD); insulin independence rates improving but lower than whole-organ; multiple donors usually needed (CIT protocol). **Newer**: islet auto-transplantation post-pancreatectomy (chronic pancreatitis); stem cell-derived islet therapy (Vertex VX-880 + others in trial).', NULL,
  'hard', 'endocrine_metabolic', 'review',
  'surgery', 'integrative', 'endocrine_metabolic', 'adult',
  'OPTN/UNOS Policies; Gruessner AC + Sutherland DE Pancreas Transplant Outcomes; AST/ASTS Guidelines', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
from public.mcq_subjects s
where s.name = 'surg_integrative'
  and s.audience = 'board'
  and not exists (
    select 1 from public.mcq_questions q
    where q.exam_source = 'AI-generated-board-seed'
      and q.board_specialty = 'surgery'
      and q.scenario = 'ผู้ป่วยอายุ 25 ปี Type 1 DM uncontrolled HbA1c 11.4 + multiple admit DKA + history of acute MI 1 year ago + ESRD on dialysis 2 years

Referral for kidney + pancreas transplant evaluation

คำถาม: pre-transplant workup + integrative considerations'
  );

