select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'Basic science: medical genetics + hereditary cancer syndromes

คำถาม: hereditary cancer syndromes + surgical implications', '[{"label":"A","text":"Cancer is always sporadic"},{"label":"B","text":"**Hereditary cancer syndromes — surgical implications**: (1) **HBOC (Hereditary Breast Ovarian Cancer) — BRCA1/2**: - Lifetime breast cancer 45-72% (BRCA1) / 45-69% (BRCA2); ovarian 39-44% / 11-17% - Risk-reducing mastectomy (RRM) — reduces breast Ca 90%+ - Risk-reducing salpingo-oophorectomy (RRSO) — at 35-40 (BRCA1) / 40-45 (BRCA2) after childbearing; reduces ovarian Ca > 80% + breast Ca ~ 50% (if premenopausal) - PARP inhibitors (olaparib, talazoparib) — adjuvant high-risk + metastatic - Increased pancreatic + prostate (BRCA2 esp), male breast (BRCA2), melanoma (BRCA2); (2) **Lynch Syndrome (HNPCC) — MLH1, MSH2, MSH6, PMS2, EPCAM**: - Colorectal lifetime 50-80% - Endometrial 40-60%, ovarian, gastric, small bowel, urothelial, brain, sebaceous skin (Muir-Torre) - Surveillance: colonoscopy q1-2 yr from 20-25; gynecologic surveillance; consider prophylactic hysterectomy + BSO after childbearing - Total colectomy with IRA if cancer diagnosed (synchronous + metachronous risk) - Immunotherapy (anti-PD-1 — pembrolizumab) for MSI-H/dMMR cancers — striking responses; (3) **FAP (Familial Adenomatous Polyposis) — APC gene**: - Colorectal cancer near 100% if untreated by 35-45 - Prophylactic total colectomy (with IRA — ileorectal anastomosis) or proctocolectomy with IPAA - Duodenal adenoma + cancer surveillance (EGD with side-viewer) - Desmoid tumor risk (especially attenuated FAP) - Thyroid Ca, brain tumor (Turcot variant), hepatoblastoma, osteoma, fibroma; (4) **MEN1 (Menin)**: - Parathyroid (primary HPT) - Pituitary adenoma - Pancreatic neuroendocrine (gastrinoma, insulinoma, others) - Adrenal, foregut carcinoid - Genetic counseling + screening - Parathyroidectomy + pancreaticoduodenectomy timing case-by-case; (5) **MEN2 (RET)**: - **MEN2A**: medullary thyroid Ca (MTC) + pheochromocytoma + parathyroid - **MEN2B**: MTC + pheo + mucosal neuromas, marfanoid - **Familial MTC** only - Prophylactic thyroidectomy in MEN2A by 5 yr, MEN2B by 1 yr - Pheochromocytoma screening lifelong; (6) **VHL (Von Hippel-Lindau)**: clear cell renal carcinoma, hemangioblastoma (CNS, retina), pheochromocytoma, pancreatic NET, endolymphatic sac tumor — multi-system surveillance + intervention; (7) **NF1 (Neurofibromatosis 1)**: neurofibromas, MPNST risk, pheochromocytoma, optic glioma, etc.; (8) **NF2**: vestibular schwannomas bilateral, meningioma; (9) **TP53 (Li-Fraumeni)**: sarcoma, breast, brain, adrenocortical, leukemia — multi-cancer; intensive surveillance (whole-body MRI); (10) **CDH1 (Hereditary Diffuse Gastric Ca)**: gastric (diffuse-type) + lobular breast — prophylactic total gastrectomy considered + breast surveillance/RRM; (11) **PTEN (Cowden)**: breast, thyroid, endometrial, renal, colon, melanoma — surveillance + selective intervention; (12) **STK11 (Peutz-Jeghers)**: GI hamartomatous polyps, breast, ovarian, pancreatic, cervical Ca; (13) **Genetic counseling + cascade testing of family** — essential"},{"label":"C","text":"No screening needed"},{"label":"D","text":"Surgery always avoided"},{"label":"E","text":"Single approach for all"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Hereditary cancer syndromes** — ~ 5-10% of all cancers; genetic testing increasingly accessible (NGS multi-gene panels). Each syndrome has specific cancer profile + surveillance + risk-reduction options. **NCCN Guidelines for Genetic/Familial High-Risk Assessment** — detailed criteria for testing. Increasingly: ''all-comer'' testing in certain cancers (pancreatic, ovarian, triple-negative breast, prostate metastatic) regardless of family history. **Major syndromes** (described above) — surgical implications: 1. **HBOC** (BRCA1/2): RRM, RRSO 2. **Lynch**: extensive colon resection if cancer; prophylactic hysterectomy + BSO after childbearing; intensive surveillance 3. **FAP**: prophylactic colectomy mandatory by 20s; subtotal with IRA vs total proctocolectomy + IPAA; duodenal surveillance 4. **MEN1**: pancreatic + parathyroid surgery timing 5. **MEN2**: prophylactic thyroidectomy in childhood; pheo workup before any surgery 6. **CDH1**: prophylactic total gastrectomy considered; breast surveillance/RRM 7. **VHL**: intervention for selected RCCs (nephron-sparing), hemangioblastoma, pheo 8. **Li-Fraumeni**: cancer-by-cancer; intensive surveillance whole-body MRI **Genetic counseling principles**: - Pre-test counseling: implications, limitations, alternatives - Variant interpretation (pathogenic, likely pathogenic, VUS, benign) — VUS management challenging - Cascade testing of family — important for risk stratification - Reproductive options (PGT — preimplantation genetic testing) - Psychosocial + insurance considerations (GINA US protects against insurance discrimination — health, not life or long-term care) **Polygenic risk scores (PRS)** — emerging for common cancers; combines multiple low-penetrance SNPs; may augment surveillance decisions; not standard yet. **Multi-gene panel testing** — practical efficiency vs single-gene; identifies syndromes beyond what''s clinically suspected; manage incidental findings.', NULL,
  'hard', 'hemato_onco', 'review',
  'surgery', 'basic_science', 'hemato_onco', 'adult',
  'NCCN Genetic/Familial High-Risk Assessment; ACMG Practice Guidelines; ASCO Genetic Testing', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
from public.mcq_subjects s
where s.name = 'surg_basic_science'
  and s.audience = 'board'
