select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'Basic science: pediatric surgical anatomy + congenital anomalies

คำถาม: common congenital anomalies + presentations', '[{"label":"A","text":"All anomalies have same presentation"},{"label":"B","text":"**Common pediatric surgical congenital anomalies**: (1) **GI tract**: - **Esophageal atresia ± TEF** — drooling, choking, can''t pass NG; types I-V Gross - **Pyloric stenosis** — 2-12 wk, projectile non-bilious vomiting, olive RUQ, hypochloremic hypokalemic metabolic alkalosis - **Duodenal atresia** — bilious vomiting day 1, ''double bubble'' X-ray (gas in stomach + duodenum proximal), 30% Down syndrome - **Malrotation ± volvulus** — bilious vomiting newborn, corkscrew on UGI = surgical emergency - **Jejunoileal atresia** — bilious vomiting, distention, no distal gas - **Meconium ileus** — distal SBO at birth, microcolon, 80% CF - **Hirschsprung disease** — failure to pass meconium > 48h, distention, biopsy aganglionosis - **Anorectal malformation** — imperforate anus spectrum; associated VACTERL; cloacal in female - **Necrotizing enterocolitis** — preterm, pneumatosis intestinalis, portal venous gas, perforation - **Meckel diverticulum** — ''rule of 2''s'' (2% population, 2 ft proximal IC valve, 2 in long, 2 yr presents, 2:1 M:F); painless GI bleed, intussusception, obstruction; technetium scan; (2) **Abdominal wall**: - **Gastroschisis** — right paraumbilical, no membrane - **Omphalocele** — midline, membrane, associations (cardiac, chromosomal) - **Umbilical hernia** — usually close by 5 yr - **Inguinal hernia** — patent processus vaginalis, repair to prevent incarceration; (3) **Hepatobiliary**: - **Biliary atresia** — progressive jaundice in infant, conjugated bilirubinemia, light stool, dark urine; Kasai portoenterostomy by 60-90 days improves outcome but most progress to liver transplant - **Choledochal cyst** — types I-V (Todani); cystic dilation of biliary tree; risk cholangiocarcinoma; cyst excision + Roux-en-Y hepaticojejunostomy; (4) **Genitourinary**: - **Posterior urethral valves** — boys; bladder outlet obstruction; renal damage; ablation - **Vesicoureteral reflux** — graded I-V; UTIs; surveillance vs ureteral reimplant - **Cryptorchidism (undescended testis)** — orchiopexy by 6-18 mo to preserve fertility + reduce malignancy risk - **Hypospadias** — urethral meatus on ventral; repair 6-18 mo - **Ambiguous genitalia / DSD** — multidisciplinary evaluation; CAH (adrenal hyperplasia) life-threatening; (5) **Diaphragm + thorax**: - **CDH (congenital diaphragmatic hernia)** — bowel in chest, pulmonary hypoplasia, PHTN - **Pulmonary sequestration, CCAM/CPAM** — congenital lung lesions; selective resection - **Pectus excavatum / carinatum** — chest wall deformity; Nuss bar repair or Ravitch; (6) **Neck**: - **Thyroglossal duct cyst** — midline, moves with swallowing/tongue protrusion; Sistrunk procedure - **Branchial cleft anomalies** — lateral; 2nd most common; excise tract - **Cystic hygroma / lymphatic malformation** — sclerotherapy (OK-432, doxycycline), surgery; (7) **CNS**: spina bifida, hydrocephalus, encephalocele, Chiari malformation — multidisciplinary peds neurosurgery; (8) **Cardiac**: TOF, TGA, HLHS, AVSD, VSD, ASD — pediatric cardiology + cardiac surgery; (9) **Limbs / spine**: clubfoot, hip dysplasia, scoliosis, polydactyly, syndactyly — ortho; (10) **Genetic syndromes** common — chromosomal microarray, WGS increasingly considered; multidisciplinary care"},{"label":"C","text":"No surgical interventions"},{"label":"D","text":"Same approach all ages"},{"label":"E","text":"No anatomical knowledge needed"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Pediatric congenital anomalies** — diverse surgical conditions; early recognition + appropriate intervention improves outcomes. Key principles: 1. **VACTERL** association — vertebral, anal, cardiac, tracheoesophageal, renal, limb — screen for all if one identified 2. **Trisomy associations** — Down (duodenal atresia, AVSD, Hirschsprung), Edwards (multiple anomalies), Patau 3. **Prenatal diagnosis** — increasing role of imaging + counseling 4. **Multidisciplinary teams** — peds surgery, neonatology, cardiology, neurology, urology, ortho, genetics, social work 5. **Family-centered care** — communication, support, decision-making **Selected critical conditions**: - **Bilious vomiting in newborn = malrotation with volvulus until proven otherwise** — UGI emergent - **Failure to pass meconium > 48h** — Hirschsprung, meconium ileus, meconium plug, anorectal malformation, jejunal/ileal atresia, prematurity-related - **Acholic stools + conjugated hyperbilirubinemia in infant** — biliary atresia; Kasai by 60-90 days; most progress to LT - **Imperforate anus** — physical exam at birth; cloacal complex in females; VACTERL workup - **Cryptorchidism** — by 6-18 mo orchiopexy; reduces malignancy risk (still elevated but earlier intervention improves) + preserves fertility - **NEC** — preterm, life-threatening, NPO + abx + supportive; surgery if perforation - **Intussusception** — peak 5-9 mo, lethargy + currant jelly stool + sausage RUQ; air enema reduction - **Pyloric stenosis** — projectile non-bilious vomiting, hypochloremic hypokalemic metabolic alkalosis; pyloromyotomy AFTER correcting electrolytes (not emergent surgery) **Meckel diverticulum ''rule of 2''s''** — 2% of population, 2 ft proximal to IC valve, 2 in length, presents by age 2, 2:1 M:F; painless lower GI bleed (ectopic gastric mucosa) most common; intussusception lead point; obstruction; diverticulitis; technetium-99m pertechnetate (Meckel scan) for ectopic gastric. **Biliary atresia**: progressive obliteration of extrahepatic bile ducts; presents 2-8 wk; Kasai portoenterostomy (Roux-en-Y hepaticojejunostomy) by 60-90 days for best outcomes; even with successful Kasai, ~ 70-80% eventually need liver transplant. Early recognition critical — surgical timing affects outcome. **Choledochal cyst** — Todani classification I-V; risk of cholangiocarcinoma (10-20%) — excision + Roux-en-Y reconstruction.', NULL,
  'medium', 'pediatrics', 'review',
  'surgery', 'basic_science', 'pediatrics', 'neonate',
  'APSA Pediatric Surgery Handbook; Coran AG et al. Pediatric Surgery Textbook', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
