select
  s.id, 'board', NULL, 'Integrative: post-bariatric body contouring surgery

คำถาม: integrative care of weight loss patient', '[{"label":"A","text":"Single specialty management"},{"label":"B","text":"**Post-massive weight loss body contouring — integrative**: (1) **Patient evaluation pre-contouring**: - Weight stability — typically 12-18 months post-bariatric + ≥ 6 months stable weight - Nutritional status — albumin, prealbumin, vitamins, minerals optimized - Smoking cessation absolute (4 weeks pre + post) - Glycemic control (DM) - Medical optimization (HT, OSA, comorbidities) - Psychological readiness — realistic expectations, body image, depression, eating disorders - Functional assessment + activity status; (2) **Common body contouring procedures**: - **Abdominoplasty** — most common; remove excess abdominal skin + fat + tighten rectus diastasis; outcomes good when patient stable - **Brachioplasty** — upper arm contouring; significant scar trade-off - **Thigh lift (medial / lateral)** — significant scar; functional + aesthetic benefit - **Mastopexy + augmentation** — breast lift ± augmentation for ptosis - **Lower body lift (belt lipectomy / circumferential)** — comprehensive lower body; major procedure - **Buttock augmentation** — autologous fat transfer (BBL) or implant - **Facial rejuvenation** — face/neck lift, brow lift; (3) **Staging strategy**: - Often multiple procedures over 1-3 years - Combine compatible procedures (efficiency vs complication risk) - High-risk patient → staged with longer interval; (4) **Risks specific to massive weight loss**: - Wound complications (poor healing, seroma, hematoma, dehiscence, necrosis) higher than primary cosmetic - DVT/PE high risk — pre-op assessment + chemoprophylaxis + early mobility - Long surgery + intraop hypothermia - Nutritional impact on healing - Scar burden + visibility - Patient expectations mismatch - Late recurrence with weight regain; (5) **Insurance considerations**: - Functional indications (panniculectomy for chronic intertrigo, ulceration, hygiene; not cosmetic) - Documentation of conservative therapy failure - Pre-authorization process - Out-of-pocket for purely cosmetic; (6) **Multidisciplinary**: bariatric surgery, plastic surgery, nutrition, psychology, primary care; (7) **Patient education + expectations**: - Scars are permanent + visible - Multiple procedures may be needed - Recovery time substantial - Risk of complications higher than non-bariatric counterparts - Body changes ongoing — late skin laxity; (8) **Nutritional + medical optimization throughout**: - Protein (1.5+ g/kg/day) - Multivitamins (bariatric-specific) - Lifestyle (exercise, sleep, hydration) - Glycemic + BP control; (9) **Psychological + body image**: - Pre + post-op assessment - Realistic expectations crucial - Counseling support - Continued weight management; (10) **Long-term outcomes**: body contouring contributes to weight maintenance long-term + improved quality of life + body image (multiple studies in massive weight loss population)"},{"label":"C","text":"No follow-up needed"},{"label":"D","text":"Single procedure for all"},{"label":"E","text":"Skip nutritional considerations"}]'::jsonb,
  'B', '**Post-massive weight loss body contouring surgery** — increasingly common with bariatric prevalence growth; substantial functional + aesthetic role + quality of life impact. **Pre-operative readiness**: 1. Weight stability ≥ 6-12 months post nadir 2. Nutritional optimization (especially protein, vitamins, minerals — post-bariatric patients often deficient) 3. Smoking cessation absolute (4+ weeks pre + post) — wound healing 4. Medical comorbidity optimization (DM, HT, OSA) 5. Psychological readiness — realistic expectations, body image work, treated depression/anxiety/eating disorder, support system 6. Reasonable functional + activity status **Common procedures**: 1. **Abdominoplasty** (panniculectomy) — most common; addresses excess skin + fat + rectus diastasis; functional (hygiene, mobility) + aesthetic 2. **Brachioplasty** — arm contouring 3. **Thigh lift** — medial/lateral 4. **Lower body lift / belt lipectomy** — circumferential; major 5. **Mastopexy ± augmentation** — breast 6. **Buttock contouring** — fat transfer (BBL — Brazilian Butt Lift; risks include fat embolism if injected intramuscularly), implant 7. **Facial rejuvenation** — face, neck, brow **Specific risks in massive weight loss population**: - Wound complications (poor healing, seroma, hematoma, dehiscence, necrosis) — 30-50% in some series vs lower in non-MWL - DVT/PE — major risk: longer surgery, immobility, BMI history; chemoprophylaxis + mechanical + early mobility - Nutritional deficiency impacts healing - Hypothermia in long surgeries - Higher reoperation rate **Insurance considerations**: - Panniculectomy can be functionally indicated (chronic skin intertrigo, ulceration, hygiene impairment) — may be covered with documentation - Pure cosmetic — out-of-pocket - Pre-authorization process important **Multidisciplinary collaboration**: bariatric surgery, plastic surgery, nutrition, psychology, primary care + others as needed (DM educator, sleep medicine). **Staging strategy** — multiple procedures over 1-3 years; balance combining for efficiency vs complication risk (longer surgery + larger trauma = higher complications); high-risk patients staged with longer intervals. **Realistic expectations + scar management**: scars are permanent + often extensive; realistic discussions + post-op scar care (silicone, RT for keloid-prone, time, sun protection). **Long-term outcomes**: body contouring contributes to maintained weight loss long-term + improved quality of life, body image, sexual function, exercise participation (multiple studies — Modarressi 2013, others). Psychological benefits substantial in appropriately selected patients.', NULL,
  'medium', 'endocrine_metabolic', 'review',
  'surgery', 'integrative', 'endocrine_metabolic', 'adult',
  'ASPS Body Contouring after MWL; ASMBS Position Statements; Sanger C et al. Plast Reconstr Surg', 'AI-generated-board-seed', true, 'seeded via Claude Code session (no critique pass)'
from public.mcq_subjects s
